# Woosoo Platform — Cursor AI Rules

> **EXPERIMENTAL — Cursor hybrid mode, Tier 1–2 only.**
> Source of truth: `AGENTS.md § Immutable Rules`. This file mirrors those rules for Cursor AI.
> If this file and `AGENTS.md` ever conflict, **`AGENTS.md` wins**. Keep them in sync.
>
> **Known Cursor limitation:** `.cursor/rules` files may not load reliably in multi-root
> workspaces (confirmed bug, 2025–2026). Until Phase 2 (per-app repo rules files) is complete,
> the operator MUST paste the mandatory preamble (see `docs/USAGE_GUIDE.md § Cursor Hybrid
> Workflow`) at the start of every Cursor session.

---

## Prime Directive

Correctness > speed. This system runs a live restaurant. A bad change can break ordering,
printing, and table sessions in real time.

---

## Workspace Setup

Always open via **`woosoo-platform.code-workspace`** (multi-root workspace). This keeps the
platform repo (with `docs/cases/` and `contracts/`) in scope alongside the app repo.

**Edit only the one active app's directory.** If you are asked to modify files in more than one
app in the same session: STOP, tell the operator, and request the task be split. Do not proceed
cross-app.

| App | You may edit |
|-----|-------------|
| Backend (Laravel 12) | `woosoo-nexus/**` |
| Frontend (Nuxt 3 PWA) | `tablet-ordering-pwa/**` |
| Print relay (Flutter) | `woosoo-print-bridge/**` |
| Platform governance | `docs/**`, `*.md` (excl. `.claude/agents/**`, `.claude/skills/**`), `hooks/**`, `state/**` |

---

## Immutable Rules (verbatim from `AGENTS.md`)

- **Backend owns truth.** Tablet sends only `{ guest_count, package_id, items: [{ menu_id, quantity }] }`. Never send pricing, tax, modifiers, totals, POS mapping, or order state from the tablet.
- **Order state machine:** valid states: `pending, confirmed, in_progress, ready, served, completed, cancelled, voided, archived`. Terminal: `completed | cancelled | voided | archived`. Do not invent new states. See `contracts/order-state.contract.md`.
- **No raw errors in customer-facing UI.** Friendly messages only. Stack traces, SQL errors, exception dumps → logs only.
- **No hardcoded LAN IPs or API/Reverb hosts** in tablet or bridge code. Production POS static IP is `192.168.1.32` — detect mismatches; never write it into tablet/bridge source.
- **No secrets in `.env`** without explicit operator review and backup.
- **One app per branch/commit** unless this is an explicitly approved integration-scoped change recorded in the case file.

---

## Tier 3 — STOP Immediately

If the task touches **any** of the following, STOP and tell the operator to use Claude Code's
Specialist agents instead (they have deep contract context that Cursor lacks):

- Order state machine or order lifecycle
- Session lifecycle (guest sessions, table sessions)
- Payment / pricing / tax / totals
- Printing / print jobs / print dispatch
- Auth / tokens / Sanctum / device tokens / session guards
- API contract changes (`contracts/*.md`)
- Reverb / broadcasting / WebSocket events
- Queues / schedulers / jobs / retries
- Race conditions / idempotency
- DB migrations
- Cross-app dependencies
- Production deployment

---

## Git Rules

- Do **NOT** run `git commit` — the operator reviews and commits.
- Do **NOT** run `git add .` or `git add -A` — operator stages specific files by path.
- Do **NOT** run `git reset --hard`, `git clean -fd`, or any force-push variant.
- The branch **must already be** `agent/<slug>` before you start. If it is not, tell the operator; do not create or switch branches yourself.

---

## Verification Commands

Canonical gate: `bash scripts/pre-merge-check.sh --app <name>` (run by Claude Code Verifier, not by you).

You may run these as self-checks only — they are not a substitute for the Verifier gate:

| App | Self-check commands |
|-----|---------------------|
| woosoo-nexus | `php artisan test` |
| tablet-ordering-pwa | `npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm run build` |
| woosoo-print-bridge | `flutter analyze && flutter test` |

---

## Before First Edit

Complete **PRE_EDIT_GATE** (`hooks/pre-edit-gate.md`): files table, minimal patch, non-goals, risk
review. Do not edit until done. After edits, run **POST_EDIT_REVIEW** (`hooks/post-edit-review.md`)
before the case checkpoint.

---

## Mandatory Checkpoint (your last action)

When you finish implementing, your **last action** must be to write the Specialist checkpoint to
`docs/cases/<slug>.md` in the platform repo (it is always in scope via the multi-root workspace).

Write or update these two sections:

**`## Specialist Investigation & Implementation`** — what you investigated, what you changed, why.

**`## Run State`** — refresh these fields:
```
- last_completed_agent: specialist:<agent-name>   # e.g. specialist:chuya-frontend
- next_agent: verifier
- active_runner: cursor
- status: IN_PROGRESS
- updated: <YYYY-MM-DD>
```

If you cannot locate the case file, STOP and tell the operator. Do not hand off without a checkpoint.
